featured_reviews.review_id: This is a large mosque built at an elevation of about fifteen feet from the ground and quite large. There is a lot of minute work on the minarets as well as inside the mosque. It has a mix of Hindu and Islamic architecture as there are a large of pillars inside the main hall of the mosque. On the roof, on can see very intricate art work similar that seen in Jain temples. There is a unique prayer hall for women in that mosque. There is a well-maintained garden .Well-worth visiting!

featured_reviews.review_id:
A very Historic Mosque.
Jamia Masjid Bhatkal is most popular mosque in Bhatkal. It became popular when Moulana Abdul Bari Nadvi (Rahmatullahialaih) became khateeb of this Mosque.  Moulana's mesmserising voice & the way of preaching attrracted everyone in the town. Moulana used to deleiver sermons & speeches in a most kindest & sweetest manner. May the soul of Moulana Rest in Peace.
When Moulana used to lead Jumah here, almost 10,000 people from & around Bhatkal used to attend jumah here
The mosque then became the iconic mosque in Bhatkal.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Located in interiors of Badriya Colony, Badriya Juma Masjid is a decent masjid with simple interiors.

The surrounding area is quite peaceful as there is low and infrequent movement of vehicles.

Juma khutba usually begins at around 1.20 pm and the jamaat begins at around 1.30 pm.

Friday Khutba is usually given by Maulana Abdun Noor Fakerdey, son of late Maulana Abdul Bari Nadvi.
